This paper is primarily focused on optimization methods for machine learning, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of second-order information in optimization, which is related to numerical analysis and optimization, making cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) a likely sub-category as well. The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which are commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper also discusses the design of algorithms, which is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
